[Read more about safety]

[Read more about reliability]

 
Other Cars to Consider

The Mercedes-Benz E250 BlueTEC has a turbodiesel engine that earns much better highway fuel economy estimates than the GS Hybrid. Test drivers say it has a comfortable ride and lots of back seat space. They also appreciate its luxurious cabin.

The Audi A6 impresses reviewers with its powerful turbocharged four-cylinder base engine and poised handling. They say its infotainment system is easy to use, and one of the best in the class. Additionally, with the available turbodiesel engine, the A6 gets better highway fuel economy estimates on the highway.

Compare the GS Hybrid, E-Class and A6 »
Details: 2016 Lexus GS Hybrid

The 2016 Lexus GS 450h seats five and comes with standard rear-wheel drive. Powering the GS 450h is a 3.5-liter V6 engine and two electric motors. A continuously variable automatic transmission is standard. The GS Hybrid is available in one trim, though options are available. The non-hybrid GS is reviewed separately. The GS 450h was fully redesigned for the 2013 model year and sees few changes for 2016. As a result, this overview uses applicable research and reviews from the 2013 through 2016 model years.

